How to know if a source/ online link is reliable or not?

-Have reputable domains such as edu or org or gov or some news site
-Careful of URL with excess spelling mistakes or hyphens
-Check for author's creditenals
-Check for author who are recongized experts
-Check for references as they allow you to verify their information
-Check whether it is a neutral tone( not scared to present facts and is presented in a formal manner)
-Avoid emotive language(Language which aims to evoke emotions)
-Trustworthy sites have a clean professional design with proper spellings and grammar
-Reliable sites do not bombard you with ads
-Look for user reviews or ratings
-Reliable sources provide clear contact info
-Trustworthy sites often display awards, certifications or seals of approval